parameters:
(Really, this shop is always bustling. It's... Tomitakuya,
right?)
Welcome! What a beautiful young lady we have here!

For a cute customer like you, how about this cherry blossom-
colored kimono?
Wow, it's gorgeous! Such a glamorous kimono, isn't it?

Right? It's much more vivid and splendid than the old kimono
you're wearing now, don't you think?
Does this blue kimono look old...?

Yes, indeed. Upon closer inspection, it seems quite worn.
Why not dispose of it at a second-hand shop and buy this new
one here?

...I'm sorry. This blue kimono is something precious my
father bought for me a long time ago, so I've been wearing
it ever since. If possible, I'd like to continue wearing
it...

Is that so? But new clothes are more comfortable to wear.
How about this autumn piece? It's quite fashionable right
now.
...I'm sorry for the intrusion. I'll come again later.
--Karin bowed to the shopkeeper and left the drapery store.
...What was with that girl? Just window shopping?

No, it seems she has a strong attachment to her own clothes
and left as is.

Hmph, ridiculous. That's just an excuse for being broke and
penniless. It's a waste of time to deal with people who
can't even afford our kimonos. Time is money--focus on
serving customers who will actually buy, got it?!

...Master of Tomitakuya. Isn't it about time we proceed with
that matter?

Ah, the branch store matter. We're making a profit, so we
need to expand our business further. It's about time to
tighten negotiations and head over to that dango shop.

Welcome. Are you looking for a kimono or fabric? We have a
good selection here~ Please take a look around.
Oh? Are you looking for a costume?
Yes. Do you have dance costumes here?

Ha ha! There is no attire that Tomichouya, the finest drapery
store in the land, does not have. We shall prepare whatever
you desire.
Now, which one would you like to purchase?\$

Thank you for purchasing both. We look forward to your next
visit.

Oh, it seems you already have this one. Is there anything
else you would like?

Thank you for your purchase. --Karin has obtained the
\c[17]Miko Attire\c[0]!\$
It looks like I don't have enough money on hand...

Oh, it seems you already have this one. Is there anything
else you would like?

Thank you for your purchase. --Karin has obtained the
\c[17]Bunny Outfit\c[0]!\$
It looks like I don't have enough money on hand...

Oh! Welcome, Karin-san! It seems the small theater is
thriving, isn't it?

Ahaha, thank you very much Lately, more customers have been
coming than before, and I'm so happy. I'm grateful for the
dance costumes you've sold to me.

But you are in luck. You've come at just the right time.
Actually, we just got some new costumes in yesterday.
New costumes? What kind might they be...?

Yes. \c[17]Basara Costume\c[0] and the exotic
\c[17]Dancer's Costume\c[0]. I would like to recommend
these two new products, what do you think?

Wow! Both costumes are lovely They're glamorous, easy to
wear, and perfect for dancing!

The Basara Costume is red. And this dancer's costume from
overseas is made of a beautifully colored blue fabric. How
about it? It would suit you as well as the kimono you always
wear, Karin-san.

Hmm. I do like blue... (Dad also liked blue, I wonder why...
Could it be a preference passed down through
generations...?)

The price for both is 20,000 mon. They are quite rare
costumes, so someone else might buy them. Now is the chance.
Would you like to purchase them?

(What should I do... The customers would probably be happy
with these costumes, but they're quite expensive... To buy
or not to buy...)

Understood! Please let me buy the new costumes! Could you
make out the receipt to the Iga Ninja Group?

Oh! As expected, Karin-san makes quick decisions! Please
take the costumes. Thank you for your purchase

Uh-uhm, sorry. The price is quite high, so I'll think about
it a bit more before buying...

Thank you very much for purchasing both of the dance
costumes.

Karin-san's theater is becoming quite the talk around
Nihonbashi. Please keep up the good work with your dancing!

Uh-huh, it's expensive. But it's a unique item that can't be
found elsewhere, so I want it...
Oh my! What a lovely fabric! Perhaps I shall take this one.

How about this fabric? I believe it would suit you well,
Madam.

Are you looking for some fabric? If you find something you
like in the store, please don't hesitate to call out to us.

Right now, they're cutting the fabric I want in the back. I
recommend this Tomichouya store because they have a good
selection.
Welcome! What kind of fabric are you looking for today?
...Hmm? Why do you look so surprised to see my face?

No, it's nothing! Ahaha...! (That's right, this kimono shop
is Tomitakuya's place...)

Welcome, dear customer! Our shop boasts a wide variety of
fabrics and kimonos, don't we? We pride ourselves on having
the best selection in the world. Hahaha!
Yes... Each and every item is so beautiful and dazzling...

Oh, right, right. Actually, we have some rare clothes of
foreign origin at our mansion.

That's right. They're treasures that even the Shogun has
never seen. I'm willing to show them to you specially this
time. How about it? Would you like to come to my mansion?
Go to the Tomichouya Residence \c[27][H Event]\c[0]

...Understood. I would like to see those rare foreign
clothes, so I'll accompany you to your mansion.
Oh, that makes me happy. Well then, please, this way--
--Karin went with Tomitakuya to the mansion.
I'm sorry! I have an errand to run later today...!
